<div dir="ltr">Testing last night&#39;s master tarball with &quot;make check&quot; I find that opal_lifo *hangs* on every ppc/linux system I try, including both gcc and xlc, both 32- and 64-bit CPUs and even a little-endian POWER8.<div><br></div><div>Attaching gdb to a hung yields:</div><div><br></div><div><div>(gdb) thread apply all bt full</div><div><br></div><div>Thread 1 (Thread 0xfff9e4f8f30 (LWP 32858)):</div><div>#0  0x0000000010001778 in check_lifo_consistency (lifo=0xfffde0100b8, expected_count=100)</div><div>    at /home/hargrove/SCRATCH/OMPI/openmpi-master-linux-ppc64-xlc-12.1/openmpi-dev-2014-gc8730b5/test/class/opal_lifo.c:73</div><div>        item = 0x1003d6a8190</div><div>        count = 215728334</div><div>        __func__ = &quot;check_lifo_consistency&quot;</div><div>#1  0x00000000100022e4 in main (argc=1, argv=0xfffde010688)</div><div>    at /home/hargrove/SCRATCH/OMPI/openmpi-master-linux-ppc64-xlc-12.1/openmpi-dev-2014-gc8730b5/test/class/opal_lifo.c:171</div><div>        threads = {17590531453408, 17590520967648, 17590510481888, 17590499996128, 17590489510368, </div><div>          17590479024608, 17590468538848, 17590458053088}</div><div>        item = 0x1003d6a83c0</div><div>        prev = 0xfffde0100f0</div><div>        item2 = 0x1003d6a2cf0</div><div>        start = {tv_sec = 1435767655, tv_usec = 746823}</div><div>        stop = {tv_sec = 1435767667, tv_usec = 450808}</div><div>        total = {tv_sec = 11, tv_usec = 703985}</div><div>        lifo = {super = {obj_magic_id = 16046253926196952813, obj_class = 0xfff9e431fb0, </div><div>            obj_reference_count = 1, </div><div>            cls_init_file_name = 0x10003524 &quot;/home/hargrove/SCRATCH/OMPI/openmpi-master-linux-ppc64-xlc-12.1/openmpi-dev-2014-gc8730b5/test/class/opal_lifo.c&quot;, cls_init_lineno = 96}, opal_lifo_head = {data = {</div><div>              counter = 0, item = 0x1003d6a8190}}, opal_lifo_ghost = {super = {</div><div>              obj_magic_id = 160462539261969528